23 (1) Claims of a frozen bank account or credit card.
24 (2) Fraudulent bank transactions.
25 (3) Claims of identity theft or job offerings in exchange for payments.
26 (4) Requests for payments to government agencies or companies.
27 (5) Requests for disaster relief donations or loans.
28 (6) Offers to purchase tickets for lotteries, sweepstakes, or drawings for
29 vehicles.
30 (7) Prompts to click on desktop popups, such as virus warnings or
31 communication from alleged familiar merchants.
