22 e. Some virtual currency transactions are deemed to be made when recorded on a
23 public ledger which may not be the date or time when the individual initiates the
24 transaction;
25 f. Virtual currency's value may be derived from market participants' continued
26 willingness to exchange fiat currency for virtual currency, which may result in the
27 permanent and total loss of a particular virtual currency's value if the market for
28 virtual currency disappears;
29 g. An individual who accepts a virtual currency as payment today is not required to
30 accept and might not accept virtual currency in the future;
